Label: p-AXIN:CK1alpha:GSK3B:phospho-APC (20 aa repeat region):PP2A:AMER1 complex
Comment: In this complex Axin is bound to beta-catenin.

Label: CTNNB1:p-AXIN:CK1alpha:GSK3B:phospho-ub-APC (20 aa repeat region):PP2A:AMER1 complex
Comment: In this form of the destruction complex, beta-catenin is no longer associated with Axin, but instead with phospho-(20aa) APC.

Label: CTNNB1:p-AXIN:CK1alpha:GSK3B:phospho-ub-APC (20 aa repeat region):PP2A:AMER1 complex
Comment: In this complex Axin is bound to beta-catenin.

Label: RBX1:SKP1:CUL1:beta-TrCP1:phosphorylated beta-catenin complex
Comment: B-TrCP associates with phosphorylated beta-catenin through the B-TrCP WD40 repeat region. Currently, it is unclear whether the ubiquitin ligase binds beta-catenin after it leaves the complex. It is equally possible that it binds beta-catenin while beta-catenin is still bound to Axin.
